<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="58" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,815,379,440]" box="[151,301,414,440]" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,293,414,440]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–65" captionStartId="16.[151,269,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,217,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-71@16.[151,1436,194,1862]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 58–65. Exogonia una sp. nov., male holotype: (58) body, lateral view; (59) head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (60) pygofer, lateral view; (61) valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; (62) connective and style, dorsal view; (63) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (64) paraphyses, lateral view; (65) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321380/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">Figs 58–65</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,491,1678]" box="[151,539,491,518]" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,250,491,517]" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">Length:</emphasis>
Male 
<typeStatus box="[325,431,492,518]" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">holotype</typeStatus>
, 7.2 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,491,1678]" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,386,530,556]" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">
Male 
<typeStatus box="[270,381,530,556]" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Head (
<figureCitation box="[475,615,530,556]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–65" captionStartId="16.[151,269,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,217,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-71@16.[151,1436,194,1862]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 58–65. Exogonia una sp. nov., male holotype: (58) body, lateral view; (59) head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (60) pygofer, lateral view; (61) valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; (62) connective and style, dorsal view; (63) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (64) paraphyses, lateral view; (65) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321380/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">Figs 58, 59</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, well produced anteriorly, anterior margin narrowly rounded; apical portion, in lateral view, slightly directed dorsally; crown with median length 4/5 interocular width and 1/2 transocular width; surface with shallow median fovea; epicranial suture distinct basally, temporal and frontogenal sutures slightly visible. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[929,1078,646,672]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–65" captionStartId="16.[151,269,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,217,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-71@16.[151,1436,194,1862]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 58–65. Exogonia una sp. nov., male holotype: (58) body, lateral view; (59) head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (60) pygofer, lateral view; (61) valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; (62) connective and style, dorsal view; (63) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (64) paraphyses, lateral view; (65) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321380/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">Figs 58, 59</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, with width approximately equal to transocular width. Forewings (
<figureCitation box="[816,905,685,711]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–65" captionStartId="16.[151,269,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,217,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-71@16.[151,1436,194,1862]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 58–65. Exogonia una sp. nov., male holotype: (58) body, lateral view; (59) head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (60) pygofer, lateral view; (61) valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; (62) connective and style, dorsal view; (63) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (64) paraphyses, lateral view; (65) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321380/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
) with membrane distinct on apical portion, including apical cells.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,491,1678]" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">
Ground color of dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[507,647,762,788]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–65" captionStartId="16.[151,269,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,217,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-71@16.[151,1436,194,1862]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 58–65. Exogonia una sp. nov., male holotype: (58) body, lateral view; (59) head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (60) pygofer, lateral view; (61) valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; (62) connective and style, dorsal view; (63) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (64) paraphyses, lateral view; (65) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321380/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">Figs 58, 59</figureCitation>
) dark brown. Crown with small apical yellow macula. Pronotum with transverse yellow macula on anterior two-thirds. Forewings (
<figureCitation box="[937,1025,801,827]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–65" captionStartId="16.[151,269,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,217,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-71@16.[151,1436,194,1862]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 58–65. Exogonia una sp. nov., male holotype: (58) body, lateral view; (59) head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (60) pygofer, lateral view; (61) valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; (62) connective and style, dorsal view; (63) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (64) paraphyses, lateral view; (65) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321380/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
) dark brown with two pale yellow maculae; anterior one transcommissural, occupying anterior portion of clavus; posterior one on corium, extending from apical portion of claval sulcus to apex of outer discal cell and base of median anteapical cell; apical cells hyaline. Frons with broad pale yellow macula on superior portion extending to anterior margin of crown and antennal ledges, median portion brown, lateral and inferior portions dark brown; clypeus dark brown with pair of yellowish-brown lateral maculae, apex yellow; lateral portions of face dark brown. Lateral portions of thorax and venter brown; legs pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,491,1678]" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[306,394,1072,1098]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–65" captionStartId="16.[151,269,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,217,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-71@16.[151,1436,194,1862]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 58–65. Exogonia una sp. nov., male holotype: (58) body, lateral view; (59) head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (60) pygofer, lateral view; (61) valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; (62) connective and style, dorsal view; (63) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (64) paraphyses, lateral view; (65) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321380/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, almost twice as long as subgenital plates; macrosetae on apical portion, extending anteriorly along ventral margin; apical portion with ventral inner process bearing numerous setae. Subgenital plates (
<figureCitation box="[375,465,1149,1175]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–65" captionStartId="16.[151,269,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,217,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-71@16.[151,1436,194,1862]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 58–65. Exogonia una sp. nov., male holotype: (58) body, lateral view; (59) head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (60) pygofer, lateral view; (61) valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; (62) connective and style, dorsal view; (63) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (64) paraphyses, lateral view; (65) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321380/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
), in ventral view, gradually tapered toward apex; basal portion with short lateral lobe; ventral surface with macrosetae near outer margin. Styles (
<figureCitation box="[901,989,1188,1214]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–65" captionStartId="16.[151,269,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,217,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-71@16.[151,1436,194,1862]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 58–65. Exogonia una sp. nov., male holotype: (58) body, lateral view; (59) head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (60) pygofer, lateral view; (61) valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; (62) connective and style, dorsal view; (63) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (64) paraphyses, lateral view; (65) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321380/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, extending posteriorly beyond apex of connective; with small external median lobe; apical portion beyond lobe curved, with few setae; apex foot-shaped. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[596,685,1265,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–65" captionStartId="16.[151,269,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,217,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-71@16.[151,1436,194,1862]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 58–65. Exogonia una sp. nov., male holotype: (58) body, lateral view; (59) head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (60) pygofer, lateral view; (61) valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; (62) connective and style, dorsal view; (63) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (64) paraphyses, lateral view; (65) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321380/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, Y-shaped; arms basally broad. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 58–65" captionStartId="16.[151,269,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,217,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-71@16.[151,1436,194,1862]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 58–65. Exogonia una sp. nov., male holotype: (58) body, lateral view; (59) head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (60) pygofer, lateral view; (61) valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; (62) connective and style, dorsal view; (63) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (64) paraphyses, lateral view; (65) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321380/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
) with shaft, in lateral view, slightly curved ventrally, with distinct dorsoapical expanded lobe; in ventral view, base with quadrangular lateral expansion and apex expanded laterally. Paraphyses (
<figureCitation box="[1246,1389,1342,1368]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–65" captionStartId="16.[151,269,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,217,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-71@16.[151,1436,194,1862]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 58–65. Exogonia una sp. nov., male holotype: (58) body, lateral view; (59) head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (60) pygofer, lateral view; (61) valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; (62) connective and style, dorsal view; (63) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (64) paraphyses, lateral view; (65) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321380/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">Figs 64, 65</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, with anterior pair of rami broader than posterior one, directed anterodorsally in lateral view; posterior pair longer than anterior one, directed posterodorsally and with ventroapical margin serrate in lateral view; stalk approximately as long as anterior rami. Anal tube (segment X) without processes or areas bearing small setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,491,1678]" box="[197,541,1535,1562]" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,410,1535,1561]" pageId="15" pageNumber="58">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
